This project implements the architecture described in Papiri Melendez
(2026), "N-BIO: A Neuromorphic Bio-Integrated Architecture Unifying
Microtubule Cellular Automata, Astrocytic Homeostatic Gating, and Locus
Coeruleus Modulation for Robust Neuromorphic Computing"
(papers/N-BIO_arXiv_preprint.pdf). The codebase and repository are
branded KINESIS-NCA rather than N-BIO solely to avoid a naming
collision with an unrelated, pre-existing project also called N-BIO;
this is not a rebranding of the cited paper itself, which retains its
original title and authorship.

This product includes an algorithmic (not biophysical) model of
microtubule protofilament dynamics and astrocytic calcium-wave
homeostasis, structurally cross-referenced against independently
published hardware characterization work on Double-Gate Ferroelectric
FET (DG-FeFET) devices:

  - Jiang, Z., et al. (2025). A Bio-inspired Asymmetric Double-Gate
    Ferroelectric FET for Emulating Astrocyte and Dendrite Dynamics in
    Neuromorphic Systems. arXiv:2504.14466.
  - Islam, A. N. M. N. (2025). Leveraging Intrinsic Characteristics of
    Neuromorphic Ferroelectric Devices for Efficient Computing.
    PhD Dissertation, Penn State University.

